=Write a chapter for the article: {{ $('Create post title and structure').item.json.message.content.title }}, {{ $('Create post title and structure').item.json.message.content.subtitle }}, that talks about {{ $('Settings').item.json["keywords"] }}

This is the prompt for the chapter titled {{ $json.title }}: {{ $json.prompt }}.

Guidelines:
- Just return the plain text for each chapter (no JSON structure).
- Don't use markdown for formatting.
- Use HTML for formatting, but limited to bold, italic and lists.
- Don't add internal titles or headings.
- The length of each chapther should be around {{ Math.round(($('Settings').item.json.words - 120)/ $('Settings').item.json.chapters) }} words long
- Go deep in the topic you treat, don't just throw some superficial info
{{ $itemIndex > 0 ? "- The previous chapter talks about " + $input.all()[$itemIndex-1].json.title : "" }}
{{ $itemIndex > 0 ? "- The promt for the previous chapter is " + $input.all()[$itemIndex-1].json.prompt : "" }}
{{ $itemIndex < $input.all().length ? "- The following chapter will talk about " + $input.all()[$itemIndex+1].json.title: "" }}
{{ $itemIndex < $input.all().length ? "- The prompt for the following chapter is " + $input.all()[$itemIndex+1].json.prompt : "" }}
- Consider the previous and following chapters what writing the text for this chapter. The text must be coherent with the previous and following chapters.
- This chapter should not repeat the concepts already exposed in the previous chapter.
- This chapter is a part of a larger article so don't include an introduction or conclusions. This chapter should merge with the rest of the article.
